arez.spy

Interface ComputedValueInfo

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ElementInfo

    public interface ComputedValueInfo
extends ElementInfo
    A representation of a ComputedValue instance exposed to spy framework.

    • Method Detail

      • isComputing

        boolean isComputing()
        Return true if the ComputedValue is "computing". This implies that the current transaction or one of the parent transactions is calculating the ComputedValue at the moment.
        Returns:
        true if there is a transaction active.
        See Also:
        Spy.isComputing(arez.ComputedValue)

      • getPriority

        @Nonnull
Priority getPriority()
        Return the priority of the ComputedValue.
        Returns:
        the priority of the ComputedValue.

      • isActive

        boolean isActive()
        Return true if the ComputedValue is active. A ComputedValue is active if there is one or more Observers and the value will be calculated.
        Returns:
        true if the ComputedValue is active.
        See Also:
        Spy.isActive(arez.ComputedValue)

      • getObservers

        @Nonnull
List<ObserverInfo> getObservers()
        Return the list of observers for ComputedValue. The list is an immutable copy of the observers of the ComputedValue.
        Returns:
        the list of observers for ComputedValue.
        See Also:
        Spy.getObservers(arez.ComputedValue)

      • getDependencies

        @Nonnull
List<ObservableValueInfo> getDependencies()
        Return the list of dependencies of the ComputedValue. The list is an immutable copy of the dependencies of the ComputedValue. If the ComputedValue is currently being computed (i.e. isComputing() returns true) then the dependencies are provisional and may be added to as transaction completes.
        Returns:
        the list of dependencies for ComputedValue.
        See Also:
        Spy.getDependencies(arez.ComputedValue)

      • getComponent

        @Nullable
ComponentInfo getComponent()
        Return the component for the ComputedValue. This method should not be invoked if Arez.areNativeComponentsEnabled() returns false.
        Returns:
        the component that contains ComputedValue if any.
        See Also:
        Spy.getComponent(arez.ComputedValue)

      • getValue

        @Nullable
Object getValue()
                   throws Throwable
        Return the value of the ComputedValue. This method should only be invoked if Arez.arePropertyIntrospectorsEnabled() returns true.
        Returns:
        the value of the ComputedValue.
        Throws:
        Throwable - if the property accessor throws an exception.
        See Also:
        Spy.getValue(arez.ComputedValue)
